<div id="review_2629268191" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2629268191" />
    <a title="Stephen Howell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5875825-stephen-howell"><img alt="Stephen Howell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1486929442p2/5875825.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2629268191?book_show_action=true">Aug 21, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Stephen Howell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Stephen Howell" href="/user/show/5875825-stephen-howell">Stephen Howell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780093080400" href="/book/show/3386324-wolf-among-wolves">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2629268191" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17824077600613280698">I am so glad to have ‘discovered’ this book and it’s author, Hans Fallada. It’s a epic work, nearly 800 pages but I did not want it to finish. He is a great storyteller, making you really care about the characters and the style of his writing is like a movie script or screenplay. He depicts life in 1920’s Germany so vividly, you picture it so clearly in your mind. It may help to have an interest in that period of Germany’s history, The Weimar years, which I currently have but the story could eas</span>
  <span id="freeText17824077600613280698" style="display:none">I am so glad to have ‘discovered’ this book and it’s author, Hans Fallada. It’s a epic work, nearly 800 pages but I did not want it to finish. He is a great storyteller, making you really care about the characters and the style of his writing is like a movie script or screenplay. He depicts life in 1920’s Germany so vividly, you picture it so clearly in your mind. It may help to have an interest in that period of Germany’s history, The Weimar years, which I currently have but the story could easily be set in today’s era. Troubled times, desperate people but ultimately a story of personal growth and courage. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17824077600613280698" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


