    <a title="Derek" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/9540548-derek"><img alt="Derek" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1575956553p2/9540548.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2584226449?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Derek" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Derek" href="/user/show/9540548-derek">Derek</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2584226449" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11184238190390025990">&quot;Wolfgang Pagel reflected that, not long ago, he had thought with pride: &apos;I&apos;m not tied to anything; I can do what I want; I am free...&apos; Yes, Wolfgang Pagel--now you understand: you were free, unfettered like a wild animal. But humanity is not about doing what you want, but rather about doing what you must.&quot; <br/><br/>This is one hefty novel. It is a novel of deceit, of desire, of destruction, but most of all, of survival. <br/><br/>If you&apos;re someone who loves Netflix&apos;s Babylon Berlin, European history, or just a go</span>
  <span id="freeText11184238190390025990" style="display:none">"Wolfgang Pagel reflected that, not long ago, he had thought with pride: 'I'm not tied to anything; I can do what I want; I am free...' Yes, Wolfgang Pagel--now you understand: you were free, unfettered like a wild animal. But humanity is not about doing what you want, but rather about doing what you must." <br /><br />This is one hefty novel. It is a novel of deceit, of desire, of destruction, but most of all, of survival. <br /><br />If you're someone who loves Netflix's Babylon Berlin, European history, or just a good plot-driven novel, then this is a must-read. Caution: it is 803 pages in length at tight-set print, so one ought to be prepared to spend many hours with this text. The read is itself the reward, however. <br /><br />I am so glad that I have stumbled across Fallada, and I look forward to reading Every Man Dies Alone later on this year. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11184238190390025990" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
