<span id="freeTextContainer7671317567460927995">I got about 100 pages into this and I just couldn&apos;t continue. There was some excellent writing and some interesting scenes about the poverty and degeneration of Germany as the economy slowly crumbled. What turned me off was the pacing and the fact that I couldn&apos;t keep track of any of the characters. Each chapter is divided into several sections where maybe a page and a half is told from the POV of a certain character. I felt like I was constantly jumping from one perspective to another just as I</span>
  <span id="freeText7671317567460927995" style="display:none">I got about 100 pages into this and I just couldn't continue. There was some excellent writing and some interesting scenes about the poverty and degeneration of Germany as the economy slowly crumbled. What turned me off was the pacing and the fact that I couldn't keep track of any of the characters. Each chapter is divided into several sections where maybe a page and a half is told from the POV of a certain character. I felt like I was constantly jumping from one perspective to another just as I was starting to get invested in one characters story. I would have loved to have finished this book, but there were too many elements in the writing that just turned me off to it entirely.</span>
